kosher salt. Some of them are much saltier and so you have to be careful if you use a different

They're expensive but you don't have to do it very often and then I poured in vodka. You use
very inexpensive vodka. It's no time for grey goose and I filled the jar with vanilla and vodka and
the liquid after about four or six months becomes vanilla extract and the smell is just amazing.
And also the vanilla beans, the seeds inside become liquid so you just snip off the top and you squeeze
the beans out. So if you're making something that like a vanilla pudding or a vanilla cake,
